SenseMap – Privacy Policy

Last updated: 27th November, 2025

SenseMap is an ambient awareness application that displays simple environmental information such as noise level, light level, and motion state. This Privacy Policy explains how SenseMap handles data and permissions.

1. Information We Collect

SenseMap does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.

The app processes certain sensor data only on your device, in real time:

Microphone (Noise Level Only)

SenseMap uses the microphone solely to measure ambient sound intensity (e.g., quiet, moderate, loud).

No audio is recorded, saved, or uploaded.

No audio content is analyzed, stored, or shared.

Motion Sensors (Accelerometer / Gyroscope)

Used to determine whether the device is still or in motion.

No personally identifiable information is generated or stored.

No permission is required for these sensors.

Light Sensor

Used to estimate ambient brightness (e.g., dark, dim, bright).

No personal information is collected.

No permission is required for this sensor.

2. How We Use Information

All data processed by SenseMap is used exclusively to:

Display live, on-screen ripple animations

Show environment summaries such as noise/light/motion levels

Provide a simple ambient experience within the app

SenseMap does not:

Upload sensor data to a server

Share information with third parties

Track user behavior

Build profiles based on sensor data

All processing is local to your device and disappears once the app is closed.

3. Data Storage & Transmission

SenseMap:

Stores no data on external servers

Sends no data to third parties

Does not use analytics, advertising, or tracking services

The app does not maintain logs containing personal information.

4. Permissions

SenseMap requests the following permission:

Microphone
RECORD_AUDIO


Used only to measure sound intensity in real time.
Audio content is never recorded or transmitted.

No other dangerous permissions are requested.

SenseMap does not access the microphone when the app is in the background.

5. Children’s Privacy

SenseMap is designed for general audiences and does not target children.
The app does not knowingly collect any personal information from children.

6. Third-Party Services

SenseMap does not integrate with:

Analytics platforms

Ad networks

Cloud storage providers

External SDKs that collect user data

All functionality is self-contained within the device.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

If SenseMap changes the way it handles data or adds new features that require additional permissions, this Privacy Policy will be updated. The latest version will always be published at this URL.

8. Contact

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you may contact:

